<TITLE> PM's letters, cheques handed to slain officers' wives </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 17 (bdnews24.com)  The prime minister's official condolence letters and cash cheques have started reaching the wives of army officers slain in the BDR headquarters carnage. A delegation led by state minister for science and ICT Yafes Osman handed a condolence letter and a bank cheque for Tk 10 lakh to Nusrat Nur, widow of captain Mazharul Haider Tuesday afternoon. Iqbalur Rahim MP and the prime minister's deputy press secretary Mahbubul Huq Shakil accompanied the state minister. Earlier at noon, Rahim and Shakil handed another condolence letter along with a bank cheque for the same amount to Tanni Yafta Chowdhury, widow of Lt Col Manzur Elahi Chowdhury at their home in the city. Prime minister Sheikh Hasina earlier announced Tk 10 lakh in compensation to each of the families of the army officers killed in the Pilkhana massacre. The letters and cheques will be handed to the rest of the families of deceased officers soon, said a statement issued by Shakil
